Invokes eval() method on each pair of documents from goldDocs and autoDocs. Accumulates results in res by macro-averaging.

eval

public void eval(Document goldDoc,
                 Document autoDoc,
                 EvalResult res)
          throws java.io.IOException
Compares annotations (that comprise AttributeValues) in goldDoc with those found in autoDoc. The documents must have the same source. If goldDoc==autoDoc, then only annotations whose author=='Gold' are used as gold standard, and all other annotations are evaluated against them.

Specified by:
eval in interface Evaluator
